OL,3,CWhere will your tip go? New law stops
OL,4,Cbusinesses pocketing staff tips
OL,6,F"New rules naturally come with an
OL,7,Fadministrative burden and businesses
OL,8,Fwill see some additional cost as they
OL,9,Fwork through them in practice.
OL,11,F"It's another example of costs being
OL,12,Fplaced on a sector that can least
OL,13,Fafford it, and we continue to urge the
OL,14,FChancellor to bring down hospitality's
OL,15,Fcost burden at the Budget, primarily
OL,16,Fthrough taking action to avoid the
OL,17,Fbillion-pound business rates bombshell
OL,18,Fset to hit the sector next year when
OL,19,Frelief ends."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
